Subject: Dictated Periphery Repo Clarification Source

Description: Raw preserved source for F:\.sop as the periphery repository.

& [DictatedPeripheryRepoClarificationSource] is the preserved user specification
  + [raw_text] is:
    this second layer repo is slow, background realizations of correlations that weren't originally observed in the formation of attention described in the SOP in the primary layer. so this is like a shadow of inference cast from a point of illumination that's unobserved directly, but visible in periphery. yes I described the periphery system earlier. that's what this is. the periphery repo.

  + [second_layer_repo] is F:\.sop
  + [periphery_repo] is the repo identity for slow background correlation realizations
  + [primary_layer] is the SOP layer under direct attention and change
  + [missed_correlation] is a relation not originally observed during primary attention formation
  + [inference_shadow] is visible peripheral evidence cast from an unobserved illumination point
  + [illumination_point] is the focal event, purpose, change, or inference pressure that cannot be inspected directly
  + [visible_periphery] is the indirect trace, change pattern, narrative residue, or correlation heat available to later study

  = must: name F:\.sop as the periphery repo
  = must: distinguish slow background realization from primary attention authority
  = must: preserve inference shadow as a peripheral proxy, not direct access to hidden cognition
  = must: map missed correlations back to primary-layer SOP formation when evidence exists
  - never: treat peripheral visibility as proof of the unobserved illumination point
